FORMAT: 1A

# MQTT-MANAGER API

Endpoints to perform device authentication/authorization management

# Group Device CRUD operations
## Device CRUD [/notifyDeviceChange]
### Create, update or delete device [POST]
Add, update or delete a device and a related topic on the ACL. 
If action is "delete", delete a device from the ACL and ask EJBCA 
for an updated version of the CRL.

+ Request (application/json)
  + Body
  
            { 
              "action": "create",
              "device": "device21",
              "topic" : "/middleware/221b/attrs"
            }
            
+ Response 200 (application/json)

            {
                "message": "ok",
                "status": 200
            }

+ Request (application/json)
  + Body
  
            { 
              "action": "update",
              "device": "device21",
              "topic" : "/middleware/221b/attrs"
            }

+ Response 404 (application/json)

            {
                "message": "No device with name device21 found in ACL",
                "status": 404
            }
            
+ Response 200 (application/json)

            {
                "message": "ok",
                "status": 200
            }

+ Request (application/json)
  + Body
  
            { 
              "action": "delete",
              "device": "device21",
            }
    
+ Response 503 (application/json)

            {
                "message": "Can't connect to EJBCA REST service",
                "status": 503
            }
  
+ Response 500 (application/json)

            {
                "message": "Invalid answer returned from EJBCA.",
                "status": 500
            }
  
+ Response 500 (application/json)

            {
                "message": "The CRL returned by EJBCA could not be decoded",
                "status": 500
            }
  
+ Response 404 (application/json)

            {
                "message": "No device with name device21 found in ACL",
                "status": 404
            }
  
+ Response 200 (application/json)

            {
                "message": "Device device21 removed from ACL",
                "status": 200
            }

# Group Certificate Revocation List Operations
## CRL Update [/crlupdate]
### UPDATE CRL [POST]
Receive a raw PEM CRL

+ Request (application/json)
  + Body
  
            { 
              "crl": "*base64PEMCrl*"
            }

+ Response 400 (application/json)

            {
                "status": 400,
                "message": "PEM formated CRL could not be decoded"
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

            {
                "message": "ok",
                "status": 200
            }
